Commentary Text: Chawla to Short, out Bowled!! Googly does the trick for Chawla again. Short has a wild swing, and misses it altogether. Commentary Text: Chawla to Dhawan, out Stumped!! Chawla has the last laugh! Dhawan was down the wicket to have a go at Chawla again, but he bowls a googly outside off. Beaten by the wrong 'un is the Punjab captain and the keeper completes the formalities by dislodging the bails quickly. No chance to get back in and the opener finally runs out of luck. Was dropped on a few occasions, but he fails to make the most of the opportunities. Dhawan st Ishan Kishan b Chawla 30(20) [4s-5]

Commentary Text: Nathan Ellis to Green, out Caught by Rahul Chahar!! The struggle ends for Cam Green. His bat swings would have made a perfect Geometry lesson tonight. Especially to find the angles at which he swung his bat. To all corners. But no dice! The back of the hand slower short delivery by Nathan Ellis, Green looks to slam the pull to the longest part of the ground, and instead hits it flat down the throat of Rahul Chahar at deep mid-wicket. Is this a blessing in disguise for Mumbai? Only time will tell. Green c Rahul Chahar b Nathan Ellis 23(18) [4s-4]
